></blockquote></div>    </div>   </div>   </div> <div class="refsect1 notes" id="refsect1-function.ssh2-auth-pubkey-file-notes">  <h3 class="title">注释</h3>  <blockquote class="note" style="border:1px gray solid"><p><strong class="note" style="border:1px gray solid">注意</strong>:    </p><p class="para">    The underlying libssh library doesn't support partial auths very cleanly    That is, if you need to supply both a public key and a password it will    appear as if this function has failed. In this particular case a failure    from this call may just mean that auth hasn't been completed yet. You    would need to ignore this failure and continue on and call    <span class="function">{@link ssh2_auth_password()}</span> in order to complete    authentication.   </p>  </blockquote> </div></div>
